This paper deals with rate adaptation in 802.11 WLANs, which is a topic related to network protocols and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the trade-off between throughput performance and energy efficiency, which is a topic related to system optimization and control. Therefore, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a likely category. The paper also involves analysis and experimentation, which are topics related to information theory and signal processing, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The paper also discusses the sensitivity of performance figures towards energy consumption parameters, which is a topic related to cryptography and security, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) another possible category. Finally, the paper involves designing novel rate adaptation schemes, which is a topic related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another possible category.
